About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had my set for about a year and the carry on has traveled at least 30 flights. It’s held up extremely well. It’s gorgeous and very roomy, not expandable but surprisingly this hasn’t bothered me. I never have to worry about cramming it into the overhead because it slides right in every time. About to purchase two more sets for my kids!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The manufacturer saw the plastic complaints
reviews.reviewText: I was very nervous to purchase this luggage set due to the number of people that have had trouble with the plastic protective film. I can say for sure that the plastic did not go under the hardware or wheels on any of the three suitcases that came in this set. I was pleasantly surprised that it took me less than 5 minutes to completely remove all of the film.When I first purchased, the largest suitcase was crushed on one corner. I processed the return, and it took less than 2 days to receive my replacement in perfect condition. I have not used the luggage yet, but I am very excited to. It is a more candy apple red than the pictures would leave you to believe, but personally I think this color is even better than the wine red.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Disappointing, at this point I wouldn't recommend
reviews.reviewText: I chose these because the reviews were pretty good and it was a nice looking set. Unfortunately the plastic coating ruins the looks because you can't get it off of all areas. I spent hours with tweezers trying to remove it. I also used an old credit card as a scraper which helped a little but I wrecked my nails AND my tweezers and still can't get it all off. Don't have much confidence that they will stay shiny if they had to be covered like that just for shipping.The case seems like flimsy plastic as are the handles, the zippers don't zip very smoothly; and it is NOT expandable as the description says. They aren't roomy, I filled the largest with quilts etc. just to test the wheels, it was packed full and only weighed 29 pounds. The one good thing I can say is that the wheels did move easily with that weight, although I wonder how they will do with heavier items. This was NOT what we were expecting as we thought Rockland was a good and dependable brand. I'm concerned on how these will hold up going through airlines, guess we'll be bringing duct tape along on our next trip for emergency fixes. Don't recommend these at all.
